                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" id="avengers_sng_1" hclass="sense"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a popular British television series, made in the 1960s, in which John Steed, an English <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/gentleman" title="gentleman definition"><span class="ndv">gentleman</span></a>, and his friend Emma Peel, an expert in <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/judo" title="judo definition"><span class="ndv">judo</span></a>, had slightly comic adventures fighting crime. Many people remember <span class="ebi">The Avengers</span> for Emma Peel's leather suits and Steed's <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/bowler#bowler_topg_1" title="bowler definition"><span class="ndv">bowler</span></a> hat and rolled umbrella. A less successful film was made in 1998 with Ralph Fiennes and Sean Connery.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
